"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The metric parameter in DBSCAN expects a callable that takes two arrays from X as input and returns a value indicating the distance between them. However, the get_point_distance function returns a 2D array from euclidean_distances, which is not a single value. This will cause an error when DBSCAN tries to use this function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n< return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])\\n---\\n> return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0][0]\"\n}"